<task id="task-4531" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Use OAuth 2.0 authorization in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">This section shows you how to use OAuth 2.0 authorization in Katalon Studio.</shortdesc><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">To use OAuth 2.0 authorization in Katalon Studio, do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open your web service request object.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the web service request object editor, switch to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> tab.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="700" href="../bearer-authorization/ks-840-authorization-type.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">authorization type</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Choose <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> type as <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OAuth 2.0</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="700" href="image/ks-840-oath-20.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">OAuth 2.0</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Grant Type</uicontrol> dropdown menu, select the desired grant type.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Enter the required values for the chosen grant type.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">You can also upload your data from an excel file by clicking on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Load data from Excel</uicontrol>. For <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authentication Code</uicontrol> grant type, you need to click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Request token</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To use current authorization information, click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Update to HTTP Header</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">The authorization information is added to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">HTTP Header</uicontrol>.<image width="700" href="image/ks-840-update-to-https-header.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">update to HTTP header</alt></image></result></taskbody></task>